<p>
<seg id=1> Ground control for a hot air balloon attempting a flight around the globe says that the three pilots in the balloon should fly out of Chinese airspace by Wednesday and continue to fly east across the Pacific. </seg>
<seg id=2> On Tuesday this group, flying high in the air, deviated from the flight path regulated by Chinese authorities and found themselves in political trouble. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese officials had originally ordered them to land in the Chinese jurisdiction of Tibet. However, after negotiations by English and American foreign affairs officials, China cancelled the orders. </seg>
</p>
